Azure ExpressRoute provides a private, dedicated connection between on-premise infrastructure and Azure.

Unlike VPN, it does not use the public internet.

For example, a company can connect its data center directly to Azure with high speed and low latency.

A real-life use case is financial institutions requiring secure and high-performance connectivity.

Another example is large enterprises transferring massive data between on-premise and cloud.

ExpressRoute ensures reliability, security, and performance.
